The paper deals with graph theory and optimization problems related to graph orientation. The primary focus is on maximizing or minimizing the number of ordered vertex pairs that can be reached by a directed path. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problems and provides algorithms for solving them, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG), game theory (cs.GT), and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
